---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Terms and Conditions - dustinlanders.com">
  <article class="legal-page">
    <h1>Terms and Conditions</h1>
    <p class="last-updated">Last updated: April 1, 2026</p>

    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>
      These terms govern your use of SMS/MMS messaging services operated by
      Dustin Landers ("I", "me") through a personal phone number.
    </p>

    <h2>Service Description</h2>
    <p>
      This messaging service is used to send personal notifications and group messages
      to friends and family. Messages may be sent by an AI assistant (Claude) on my
      behalf to coordinate plans, send reminders, and check in with contacts.
    </p>

    <h2>Consent</h2>
    <p>
      By providing your phone number and agreeing to receive messages, you consent to
      receive SMS/MMS messages from this number. Message frequency varies. Message and
      data rates may apply depending on your carrier plan.
    </p>

    <h2>Opting Out</h2>
    <p>
      You may opt out at any time by replying STOP to any message. After opting out,
      you will receive a confirmation message and no further messages will be sent
      unless you opt back in.
    </p>

    <h2>Help</h2>
    <p>
      For assistance, reply HELP to any message or contact me at
      <a href="mailto:dustin.landers@gmail.com">dustin.landers@gmail.com</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Liability</h2>
    <p>
      This is a personal messaging service provided as-is. I am not responsible for
      any charges from your mobile carrier related to receiving messages. I make no
      guarantees about message delivery timing or availability.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      I may update these terms at any time. Continued receipt of messages after changes
      constitutes acceptance of the updated terms.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about these terms can be directed to
      <a href="mailto:dustin.landers@gmail.com">dustin.landers@gmail.com</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page {
    max-width: 700px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .legal-page h1 {
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }
  .legal-page h2 {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .last-updated {
    color: #888;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
</style>
